==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: handler
<hw>handler</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>one who trains or
exhibits animals.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> animal trainer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>someone in charge of training an athlete (especially
a boxer) or a team.</def> <note>The term is used sometimes sarcastically
of political consultants: ⟦ldquo⟧the president's
handlers⟦rdquo⟧.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coach, manager.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handless</ent>⟦br⟧
